= ui_row do
  = ui_col num: 8  do
    = title 'Getting Started ', display_ui: false
    %h2 Install

    Add these lines in your Gemfile:
    = example do |c|
      - c.code title: 'Code' do
        :plain
          # Gemfile
          gem "ui_bibz", '~> #{ UiBibzApp::Application::VERSION }'
    Run command:
    = example  do |c|
      - c.code title: 'Terminal' do
        :plain
          bundle install
          rails generate ui_bibz:install

    %p
      <code>rails generate ui_bibz:install</code> generate a config file in <code>config/initializers/ui_bibz.rb</code>.
      %br
      <strong>Warning:</strong> If you change <code>fontawesomejs = true</code> to <code>false</code> in this file, you will execute
      <code>rake tmp:clear</code> in console to refresh files.


    %h2 Assets Install

    Put this line in: <code>/app/assets/stylesheets/applications.css</code>
    = example  do |c|
      - c.code title: 'Code' do
        :plain
          # /app/assets/stylesheets/applications.css
          *= require ui_bibz


    Put this line in: <code>/app/assets/javascripts/applications.js</code>
    = example  do |c|
      - c.code title: 'Code' do
        :plain
          # /app/assets/javascripts/applications.js
          //= require ui_bibz
          uiBibz = new UiBibz()
          # or with turbolinks
          uiBibz = new UiBibz({ turbolinks: Turbolinks })

          uiBibz.ready()

  = ui_col num: 4 do
    %div
      :markdown

        ##Compatibility

        Gem is compatible with [**Ruby**](https://www.ruby-lang.org/ "Ruby") version 2.x.x and [**Ruby On Rails**](http://rubyonrails.org/ "Rails") 4.2.x and 5.x.x.

    %div
      :markdown

        ##Simple form

        Gem is compatible with [simple_form](#{ simple_form_path }).
        All inputs fields can be used with this [gem](https://github.com/plataformatec/simple_form).
